axb6 {leads to a typical structure, in which White's extra pawn is unimportant.
Here is an example from the Foros tournament:} 15. c4 Qb8 16. Rc3 Rc8 17. Qc2
Bf8 18. Rb1 Bc5 19. Bxc5 Rxc5 20. Nc1 Qc7 21. Nb3 Rc6 22. Nd2 {1/2-1/2 Van
