of White's first rank![%cal Rd6d3,Rc6b4]} 25. Qxc6 (25. Bb5 Nb4 26. Qa4 a6 $1
$19) 25... Qxc6 $2 {Black gains a pawn in this endgame but unfortunately, he
misses} (25... Qxd3 $1 26. Ng3 Rc8 27. Qxc8+ Bxc8 28. Rxc8+ Kg7 {winning the
a2 pawn and the game}) 26. Rxc6 Rxd3 27. f4 $6 {White destroys his own
position. After} (27. f3 Bxa2 (27... Ra3 28. Nc3 {leading to the rook endgame})
28. Rc5 {he could have defended tenaciously.}) 27... Bg4 28. Nc3 exf4 29. Nd5
